Health Policy & Admin ManagementMDG6 (Control of HIV/AIDs,

tspan.tspan: SOURCE:
This informaton was extracted on 13/02/2012 from the Creditor Reportng System(CRS)
database maintained by the Organizaton for Economic Co-operaton and Development (OECD), Statstcs
Department (htp://stats.oecd.org/Index.aspx).
DEFINITIONS:
CRS ﬁnancial data presented here are commitments and disbursements. A commitment
is a ﬁrm writen obligaton by a government or oﬃcial agency, backed by the appropriaton or availability
of the necessary funds, to provide resources of a speciﬁed amount under speciﬁed ﬁnancial terms and
conditons and for speciﬁed development purposes. A disbursement is the release of funds to, or the
purchase of goods or services for, a recipient; by extension, the amount thus spent. Disbursements
record the actual internatonal transfer of ﬁnancial resources, or of goods or services valued at the cost
to the donor. It can take several years to disburse a commitment. Yearly commitments and
disbursements are presented in constant 2009 US$ to ensure comparability over years. ODA for health
volumes are also presented in US$ per capita per year and according to allocaton (i.e. policy purpose).
Policy purposes used here are based on the original CRS statstcal purpose codes, but have been
aggregated to reﬂect, as far as possible, global health development benchmarks (i.e. MDG6;
Reproductve Health & Family Planning).
